Hello, my team is currently trying to get our Auto working in comp, but we’re having issues running named commands. We tripled checked if we mistyped the names on Pathplanner and that’s not the issue. What we see during Auto is that the Robot will follow its path, but it won’t execute any of the commands (Go L4, shoot, etc).

image1241×693 42.7 KB

For example, here we would see the robot go forward and stop. We thought we solved the issue by building the autos in robot container, but now it only raises the elevator to L4 and stops. Now mind you, our L4 works in tele-op. Here’s our GitHub (Our code is on the TrapezoidProfile Branch): 2025-Reefscape/src/main/java/frc/robot/RobotContainer.java at TrapezoidProfile · Talon-Inc/2025-Reefscape · GitHub Any Help is Greatly Appreciated

Yes we logged every command, and they showed that they finished. But it doesn’t move to the next path/command. We found that this issue happens with paths as well. For example, we have a sequential command group that runs an elevator to home command and its next sequence command is a path which does not execute. Mind you the setHome command was logged, and it showed that it finished.

image1279×705 102 KB

As you can see on the left panel in the picture above the setHome command finished, but our next path didn’t execute despite the command finishing. Also, these aren’t the first commands that are being executed, this is in the middle of our auto routine.

I think your NamedCommand may not be correct. We’ve had to register them as a new command like this

Instead of:
NamedCommands.registerCommand(“shootCoral”, shootCoral);

Try something like:
NamedCommands.registerCommand(“shootCoral”, new shootCoral(shooter));
